In this letter, President Barack Obama announces a change in the export controls for high-performance computers. He notifies the chairman of his decision to establish a new level for the notification procedure for digital computers, increasing it from the current level of 3.0 Weighted TeraFLOPS to 8.0 Weighted TeraFLOPS. This decision is based on the recommendations of the Departments of State, Defense, Commerce, and Energy. The attached report provides the rationale behind this decision, as required by Public Law 105-85, sections 1211(d) and (e).